Prototype 1: Offline Smart Pastoral Assistant
Overview

Prototype 1 demonstrates the core functionality of an offline livestock monitoring and hazard detection system.

The prototype simulates livestock collar data, processes animal information locally, detects potential danger zones, and generates grazing safety recommendations without internet dependency.


Implemented Features

- Livestock ID tracking
- Location-based risk detection
- Offline hazard analysis
- Automated alert generation
- Grazing safety recommendation

Current Technology
Python
Pandas
Machine Learning Model
Offline decision logic
CSV-based livestock dataset
